    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nBoth `nvim_buf_get_offset(0,0)` and `line2byte(line(\"$\")+1)` can not distiguish between an empty buffer and a buffer with just one newline.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n~~~sh\r\ntouch empty\r\necho > newline\r\nprintf ' ' > space\r\nfor f in empty newline space; do\r\n  nvim --headless --clean -c 'echo bufname() nvim_buf_get_offset(0,0) line2byte(line(\"$\")+1) \"\\n\"' -c q $f\r\ndone\r\n~~~\r\nresult for neovim@master:\r\n~~~\r\nempty 0 2\r\nnewline 0 2\r\nspace 0 3\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nResult for neovim 0.9.2\r\n~~~\r\nempty -1 -1\r\nnewline 0 2\r\nspace 0 3\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n since b051b13\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nVIM 9.0 patches 1-1811: \r\n~~~\r\nvim --clean empty newline space -c 'argdo echo bufname() line2byte(line(\"$\")+1)'\r\n~~~\r\nreturns \r\n~~~\r\nempty -1\r\nnewline 2\r\nspace 3\r\n~~~\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux / NixOS\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nalacritty\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nalacritty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nnix build github:neovim/neovim?dir=contrib",
