            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Currently I am using lua's io.read as a workaround, this is compatible with v0.9.2 and master\r\n~~~lua\r\n-- Check if the current buffer is empty\r\nlocal function check_empty()\r\n  if nvim.nvim_buf_get_offset(0, 0) <= 0 then\r\n    local handle = io.open(nvim.nvim_buf_get_name(0))\r\n    local eof = handle:read(0)\r\n    handle:close()\r\n    if eof == nil then\r\n      return true\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\n  return false\r\nend\r\n~~~",
